This article is a presidential proclamation by Barack Obama declaring March 2016 as Women's History Month. The proclamation recognizes the contributions of women throughout history and honors their legacies. It highlights the progress made in achieving gender equality, such as the Lilly Ledbetter Fair Pay Act and the opening of military jobs for women. However, it also acknowledges that work still needs to be done, including passing the Paycheck Fairness Act and addressing the underrepresentation of women in STEM fields. The article concludes by inviting Americans to observe Women's History Month and International Women's Day and providing a website to learn more about women's history.